The Vice President, Mike Pence, delivered remarks at a Honorable Carry Ceremony at Joint Base Pearl Harbor-Hickam in Hawaii. The ceremony was held to receive 55 flag-draped cases believed to contain the remains of American soldiers who fell in the Korean War. Pence expressed gratitude to President Trump for securing a promise from North Korean leader Kim Jong Un to return the remains of fallen U.S. service members. He emphasized the importance of accounting for all the fallen heroes and bringing them home. Pence also highlighted the bravery and sacrifices made by American soldiers during the Korean War, and expressed hope that the families of the missing fallen would find closure. He concluded by honoring the memory of the fallen and expressing gratitude to all those who have served in the military.